%R	134	2076436	34281			UVS instrument systems engineering activities. Includes requirements management, verification, resource management and integrated instrument engineering.	
%R	134	2076437	34281			Level of effort activity for instrument system engineer to support daily project activities.	
%R	134	2076440	34281			Instrument specification development and DOORS maintenance of spec.	
%R	134	2076441	34281			Instrument level analyses not related to a specific subsystem. includes thermal, structural, radiation, contamination control.	
%R	134	2076449	34281			Instrument verification activities including verification matrix maintenance, closeout reports, and verification status reporting.	
%R	134	2076459	34281			UVS Product Assurance. Includes instrument safety, reliability and quality assurance.	
%R	134	2076463	34281			UVS quality assurance. Includes quality engineering support, inspection support, test support, MRB support and coordination with Juno project quality.	
%R	134	2076466	34281			UVS EEE parts engineering. includes parts selection criteria, screening requirements, source control drawing and GIDEP alert support.	
%R	134	2076496	34281			UVS instrument mechanical. Includes all mechanical elements such as telescope housing, e-box, fabrication assembly and test support.	
%R	134	2076574	34281			UVS detector electronics. Includes requirements and spec development, schematics, PWB artwork, fabrication, assembly and test support.	
%R	134	2076578	34281			UVS optics support. Includes spec development, component spec development, component procurement, optics assembly and test support.	
%R	134	2076592	34281			UVS flight model I&T. Includes test procedure development, fixture and cable development, scripts development, as well as test execution and documentation.	
%R	134	2076593	34281			UVS engineering model I&T. includes EM test procedures, test fixtures, cables and scripts as well as test execution and documentation.	
%R	134	2076640	34281			UVS support to the Juno mission assembly, test and launch operations.	
%R	134	2076642	34281			UVS instrument team support to the Juno mission assembly and test operations with the spacecraft.	
%R	134	2076643	34281			UVS instrument team support to the Juno mission spacecraft checkout and KSC and for in-flight commissioning.	
